                                         "is_bundle":  0,
                                         "bundle_products":  [

                                                             ],
                                         "image":  "https://d3ckuu7lxvlwp2.cloudfront.net/products/01K925D2A93R2HJAGNY22EG7EY.jpg",
                                         "alt_img_1":  "products_alt_img/01K925D2F3BSA7HWD722BMCQ4C.webp",
                                         "alt_img_2":  null,
                                         "alt_img_3":  null,
                                         "alt_img_4":  null,
                                         "images":  null,
                                         "brief_info":  "Moxie Paracetamol Suspension for Kids is a pleasantly flavored oral suspension (liquid medicine) specifically formulated to provide rapid relief from pain and fever in babies and children aged 0 to 12 years.",
                                         "description":  "\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMoxie Paracetamol Suspension for Kids\u003c/strong\u003e\u0026nbsp;containing the active ingredient Paracetamol (Acetaminophen) at a concentration of \u003cstrong\u003e120 mg/5 ml\u003c/strong\u003e, this Over-the-Counter (OTC) product is a highly effective analgesic (pain reliever) and antipyretic (fever reducer). The liquid form, supplied with an accurate measuring device, ensures precise dosing and easy administration, which is vital for pediatric care.\u003c/p\u003e",
                                         "how_to_use":  "\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003cstrong\u003eDosage of Moxie Paracetamol Suspension for Kids\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWARNING: Always base the dose on the child\u0027s age and weight, and never exceed the stated dose.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAdministration:\u003c/strong\u003e For oral use only. Shake the bottle for at least 10 seconds before use. Always use the measuring spoon or syringe supplied with the pack to ensure accuracy.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBest Time to Take It:\u003c/strong\u003e Can be taken with or without food.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDosing Interval:\u003c/strong\u003e The usual interval is every 4 to 6 hours, as needed.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMaximum Dose:\u003c/strong\u003e Do not give more than 4 doses in any 24-hour period.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOverdose Guidance:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eImmediate medical advice must be sought in the event of an overdose, even if the child appears well.\u003c/strong\u003e This is due to the risk of delayed, serious liver damage.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e",
                                         "specification":  "\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePack Size:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eMoxie Paracetamol Suspension for Kids\u003c/strong\u003e (120 mg/5 ml) is typically supplied in a \u003cstrong\u003e100 mL bottle\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e",
                                         "famasi_advice":  "\u003ch3\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eContraindications of Moxie Paracetamol Suspension for Kids\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eDo \u003cstrong\u003eNOT\u003c/strong\u003e give \u003cstrong\u003eMoxie Paracetamol Suspension\u003c/strong\u003e if the child:\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDrug Allergies:\u003c/strong\u003e Is allergic (hypersensitive) to Paracetamol or any of the inactive ingredients (e.g., colorants or preservatives).\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConcurrent Medication:\u003c/strong\u003e Is taking \u003cstrong\u003eany other product that contains paracetamol\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrgan Impairment:\u003c/strong\u003e Has severe liver problems or severe kidney problems.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHereditary Intolerance:\u003c/strong\u003e Has a rare genetic disorder like hereditary fructose intolerance (HFI), as the suspension may contain fructose-releasing sugars.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003ch3\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSide Effects of Moxie Paracetamol Suspension for Kids\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eParacetamol is generally well-tolerated at the correct dose, but vigilance for severe reactions is essential.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCommon Side Effects (Mild and Expected):\u003c/strong\u003e Generally rare, but may include mild stomach upset, nausea, or vomiting.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSerious but Rare Side Effects (Requires Immediate Medical Attention):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAllergic Reactions:\u003c/strong\u003e Rash, hives, swelling of the face, lips, tongue, or difficulty breathing.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBlood and Liver Disorders:\u003c/strong\u003e Pale skin, feeling unusually tired, unexplained bruising or bleeding, getting more infections than usual, or yellowing of the skin/eyes (jaundice).\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSevere Skin Reactions:\u003c/strong\u003e Reddening of the skin, blistering, or peeling (very rare but serious).\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat to do if side effects occur:\u003c/strong\u003e If you notice any signs of a serious allergic reaction or severe skin reaction, \u003cstrong\u003estop giving the medicine immediately and seek urgent medical help.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003ch3\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePrecautions and Warnings of Moxie Paracetamol Suspension for Kids\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBefore Starting Moxie Paracetamol:\u003c/strong\u003e Consult your doctor if the child has severe malnutrition, chronic alcoholism, or is taking the antibiotic \u003cstrong\u003eFlucloxacillin\u003c/strong\u003e, due to the risk of a serious blood and fluid abnormality (high anion gap metabolic acidosis).\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDuring Use:\u003c/strong\u003e Adhere strictly to the recommended interval (at least 4 hours) and do not give the medicine for more than 3 days without medical consultation.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDosing Accuracy:\u003c/strong\u003e Dosing should ideally be based on weight, but follow the age-based chart provided with the specific product, using the correct measuring device. Always seek a doctor\u0027s advice if the child is very small or large for their age.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
